00:22:33.719 --> 00:22:34.879
kind of like a fountain.

272
00:22:34.954 --> 00:22:36.444
Oh. Jesus.

273
00:22:36.522 --> 00:22:38.046
Well. how'd you treat it?

274
00:22:39.558 --> 00:22:42.254
Fuck that. I was never in lraq.

275
00:22:42.328 --> 00:22:44.455
Good for you. The shit they spread
around there you wouldn't believe.

276
00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:46.430
I swear to God.
I've got these lraqi eyeballs

277
00:22:46.499 --> 00:22:48.467
a friend of mine brought back
to do some studies on.

278
00:22:48.534 --> 00:22:50.661
Incredible. They were
completely milked over.

279
00:22:50.736 --> 00:22:52.260
Mustard gas--
it does that to your eyes.

280
00:22:52.338 --> 00:22:53.737
Actually. I still have those in my fridge.

281
00:22:54.874 --> 00:22:56.637
Bot fly. do you think?

282
00:22:56.709 --> 00:23:00.042
Chronic viral ulcerative lesion.

283
00:23:00.112 --> 00:23:01.773
That looks like gout.

284
00:23:03.949 --> 00:23:05.712
He's running a temperature of 105.

285
00:23:05.785 --> 00:23:07.412
- Is that bad?
- It's high.

286
00:23:07.486 --> 00:23:08.783
Bad will be 108.

287
00:23:08.854 --> 00:23:12.449
You could have a seizure.
go psychotic.

288
00:23:12.525 --> 00:23:14.755
And--and probably die.

289
00:23:15.695 --> 00:23:16.719
Say "ahh."

290
00:23:16.796 --> 00:23:19.230
- Alhh.
- Oh! Jesus!

291
00:23:19.298 --> 00:23:21.129
Oh. nice.

292
00:23:21.200 --> 00:23:22.565
Black abscessed tongue.

293
00:23:22.635 --> 00:23:25.126
All abscesses
should be drained. period.

294
00:23:31.577 --> 00:23:33.169
What are you doing?

295
00:23:34.346 --> 00:23:35.438
Shut up. Joe.

296
00:23:46.892 --> 00:23:49.520
Baby...get the needles.

297
00:23:51.297 --> 00:23:52.992
Be right there.

298
00:23:54.033 --> 00:23:56.331
Right now.

299
00:23:56.402 --> 00:23:57.266
Asshole.

300
00:24:12.184 --> 00:24:13.481
It's spreading.

301
00:24:14.453 --> 00:24:15.613
Holy shit.

302
00:24:15.688 --> 00:24:17.815
- When did you say you got this bite?
- Just now.

303
00:24:17.890 --> 00:24:19.357
See this?

304
00:24:19.425 --> 00:24:22.826
This shows the advanced stages
of gangrene and epidermal rot.

305
00:24:22.895 --> 00:24:24.556
- And this over here...
- Advanced rot?

306
00:24:24.630 --> 00:24:28.225
...shows the swelling of tissues
and the lack of any type of circulation.

307
00:24:28.300 --> 00:24:30.768
See. you're telling me
that you just got this bite?

308
00:24:30.836 --> 00:24:33.304
- Yeah. just like a half hour ago.
- What I'm seeing here

309
00:24:33.372 --> 00:24:35.670
is a deep impact wound
with several virals

310
00:24:35.741 --> 00:24:37.402
and secondary bacterials.

311
00:24:37.476 --> 00:24:40.536
and that. by the accumulation of
denuded tissue around the incision marks.

312
00:24:40.613 --> 00:24:44.982
indicates that you've had this bite
for over 14 days.

313
00:24:45.050 --> 00:24:46.711
Uh... uh. at least 14 days.

314
00:24:46.786 --> 00:24:48.014
Could that be possible?

315
00:24:48.087 --> 00:24:50.647
14 days? No way. I mean--

316
00:24:50.723 --> 00:24:52.884
Well...what is today?

317
00:24:53.859 --> 00:24:55.190
Today's Wednesday.

318
00:24:55.261 --> 00:24:57.388
The 15th.

319
00:24:58.931 --> 00:24:59.955
Of April.

320
00:25:00.032 --> 00:25:02.626
Aw. hell. Can't I just get
a tetanus shot or something?

321
00:25:03.936 --> 00:25:05.699
We gotta lose the arm. Joe.

322
00:25:05.771 --> 00:25:07.500
Lose the arm?
What do you mean. lose the arm? My arm?

323
00:25:07.573 --> 00:25:09.097
It's sppreading all the way
upp to your shoulder.

324
00:25:09.175 --> 00:25:11.905
Now. if we don't sever that arm now.
it's gonna take over your chest.

325
00:25:11.977 --> 00:25:14.070
and we can't very well
cut that off. can we?

326
00:25:14.146 --> 00:25:15.670
Well. shouldn't I get a second oppinion?

327
00:25:16.382 --> 00:25:17.644
Hi. Joe.

328
00:25:19.451 --> 00:25:21.942
I'm going to give you
a very strong anesthetic.

329
00:25:22.021 --> 00:25:24.285
so you won't feel anything
during the procedure.

330
00:25:24.356 --> 00:25:25.448
These...

331
00:25:26.358 --> 00:25:27.757
...are my friends.

332
00:25:27.827 --> 00:25:28.953
My yellow friend...

333
00:25:30.863 --> 00:25:33.263
- ...is just to take the sting off.
- Aah!

334
00:25:33.999 --> 00:25:36.263
My blue friend...

335
00:25:36.335 --> 00:25:37.825
you'll barely feel.

336
00:25:37.903 --> 00:25:42.033
That means my yellow friend
is already taking effect.

337
00:25:42.107 --> 00:25:43.597
See how fast my friends work?

338
00:25:46.212 --> 00:25:48.578
And after my red-headed friend...

339
00:25:48.647 --> 00:25:50.740
... you'll never see me again.

340
00:25:50.816 --> 00:25:52.807
...see me again. see me again.

341
00:25:59.058 --> 00:26:00.923
They all react differently.

342
00:26:06.298 --> 00:26:07.322
Now what?

343
00:26:07.399 --> 00:26:09.390
Dedicated to our own Jungle Julia--

344
00:26:09.468 --> 00:26:11.060
in loving memoy

345
00:26:23.816 --> 00:26:25.511
It's not the radiator.

346
00:26:27.152 --> 00:26:28.346
Damn it.

347
00:26:48.107 --> 00:26:49.233
All right.

348
00:26:49.308 --> 00:26:50.673
Fuckin' thing.

349
00:26:50.743 --> 00:26:52.506
Cheapp--whoa.

350
00:26:54.713 --> 00:26:55.873
Damn light.

351
00:26:56.682 --> 00:26:57.842
Ohh.

352
00:27:07.126 --> 00:27:08.957
Hey. Hey!

353
00:27:09.028 --> 00:27:10.859
Hey! Bastard!

354
00:27:10.930 --> 00:27:12.329
Bastard!

355
00:27:21.874 --> 00:27:23.398
Oh. thank God.

356
00:27:23.475 --> 00:27:24.533
Oh.

357
00:27:25.277 --> 00:27:26.437
Oh. Hey!

358
00:27:26.512 --> 00:27:28.002
Hey! Hey!

359
00:27:29.281 --> 00:27:31.306
Get outta
the fuckin' road. bitch!

360
00:27:43.295 --> 00:27:45.695
Ohh! Stop!

361
00:27:45.764 --> 00:27:46.890
Stop!

362
00:27:46.966 --> 00:27:48.763
Please! Stop!

363
00:27:51.503 --> 00:27:54.165
No! No!

364
00:28:09.521 --> 00:28:11.318
What the hell was that?

365
00:28:13.592 --> 00:28:15.617
People picking up road kill.

366
00:28:15.694 --> 00:28:17.252
What. like an armadillo?

367
00:28:18.197 --> 00:28:19.494
Deer.

368
00:28:20.299 --> 00:28:22.096
You get a lot of them around here.

369
00:28:23.335 --> 00:28:25.667
You know. I read a statistic that said...

370
00:28:25.738 --> 00:28:31.233
that the eating of venison has risen
30% in the last few years.

371
00:28:31.310 --> 00:28:33.540
60% of that's from road kill.

372
00:28:34.580 --> 00:28:36.548
People eat road kill?

373
00:28:36.615 --> 00:28:38.583
If you're driving out here
at 70 miles an hour

374
00:28:38.650 --> 00:28:40.379
and a deer darts out
in front of you.

375
00:28:40.452 --> 00:28:43.580
if you blink or brake or swerve--

376
00:28:43.655 --> 00:28:45.384
shit. you'll just kill yourself.

377
00:28:45.457 --> 00:28:46.947
So. what do you do?

378
00:28:47.026 --> 00:28:48.618
Just ppick 'em off...

379
00:28:48.694 --> 00:28:50.161
just like this.

380
00:28:50.229 --> 00:28:51.719
Send it flying away from you.

381
00:28:51.797 --> 00:28:53.287
Unacceptable.

382
00:28:53.365 --> 00:28:54.889
Not really.

383
00:28:56.301 --> 00:28:58.895
It's just a clear case of you or him.

384
00:28:58.971 --> 00:29:01.405
Or her.

385
00:29:02.241 --> 00:29:03.071
Oh. fuck!

386
00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:10.639
Aah! Aah!

387
00:29:19.992 --> 00:29:21.016
Cherry?

388
00:29:22.561 --> 00:29:26.361
I thought you said if you saw a deer.
you shouldn't fucking swerve!

389
00:29:26.432 --> 00:29:27.831
It wasn't a deer.

390
00:29:29.735 --> 00:29:32.932
Cherry! Cherry! No!

391
00:29:51.390 --> 00:29:52.550
Aah!

392
00:30:05.370 --> 00:30:06.564
Palomita.

393
00:30:10.709 --> 00:30:12.768
- Don't let her die on me. Block.
- What do we got?

394
00:30:12.845 --> 00:30:15.211
Car accident. Heavy contusions
about the torso.

395
00:30:15.280 --> 00:30:16.975
possible spinal trauma...

396
00:30:18.117 --> 00:30:19.641
one severed limb.

397
00:30:20.819 --> 00:30:22.480
Where's the leg?

398
00:30:22.554 --> 00:30:24.385
Three sickos attacked her.

399
00:30:24.456 --> 00:30:26.253
I shot at them.

400
00:30:27.759 --> 00:30:29.488
I never miss.

401
00:30:33.565 --> 00:30:35.157
They took the leg with them.

402
00:30:46.778 --> 00:30:49.372
You'll have to come with us. Wray.
We need to talk about this. you know?

403
00:30:49.448 --> 00:30:50.813
He has to sign her in.

404
00:30:50.883 --> 00:30:52.043
Do what. now?.

405
00:30:52.117 --> 00:30:54.017
Well. he's with her.
He's respponsible for her.

406
00:30:54.086 --> 00:30:57.055
He can fill this out after we talk.
Let's go.

407
00:30:59.324 --> 00:31:00.518
Okay.

408
00:31:00.592 --> 00:31:01.923
Okay! Fuck!

409
00:31:03.362 --> 00:31:04.351
Hey. Block.

410
00:31:09.868 --> 00:31:11.733
No. you do it.

411
00:31:14.039 --> 00:31:15.700
Suit yourself.

412
00:31:16.842 --> 00:31:18.605
What are you doing
with a rifle. Wray?

413
00:31:20.012 --> 00:31:21.138
Nothing.

414
00:31:21.213 --> 00:31:23.875
Just thinking about maybe doing
some hunting when the season breaks.

415
00:31:23.949 --> 00:31:25.439
Come on. Wray.

416
00:31:25.517 --> 00:31:28.042
You know you're not supppposed
to be doing that stuff anymore.

417
00:31:28.120 --> 00:31:30.054
Not even hunting?

418
00:31:30.122 --> 00:31:32.488
Not even hunting.
And you know that.

419
00:31:32.558 --> 00:31:34.150
Not with your history.

420
00:31:34.226 --> 00:31:37.354
And here I stick my neck out for you.

421
00:31:37.429 --> 00:31:39.659
I stick it out far.

422
00:31:39.731 --> 00:31:42.461
Now you've got a gal in your wrecked truck
with a missing leg?

423
00:31:43.268 --> 00:31:45.429
A missing leg that's now missing?

424
00:31:45.504 --> 00:31:47.597
And here you're saying
in front of everybody

425
00:31:47.673 --> 00:31:49.504
that someone up and snatched it?

426
00:31:49.575 --> 00:31:50.974
And that you shot at 'em with a gun

427
00:31:51.043 --> 00:31:53.136
that you never should've had
in the first pplace?

428
00:31:53.212 --> 00:31:54.474
And that now they're gone?

429
00:31:55.480 --> 00:31:57.414
What if I find the leg?

430
00:31:57.482 --> 00:31:59.746
So. now you know where it is?

431
00:31:59.818 --> 00:32:02.810
You'll tell us where it is.
give us a full confession. you're saying?

432
00:32:02.888 --> 00:32:05.015
Sheriff. can we finish
this conversation somewhere else?

433
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:06.250
My thought exactly.

434
00:32:10.762 --> 00:32:13.856
I know it sounds a little arrogant
puttin' upp a sign--

435
00:32:13.932 --> 00:32:16.423
"Best damn barbecue in Texas..."

436
00:32:16.501 --> 00:32:18.332
"Period."

437
00:32:19.905 --> 00:32:21.566
But. hell...

438
00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:23.801
who's gonna come in here
and argue about that?

439
00:32:26.078 --> 00:32:28.876
Oh. yeah.
Big contest comin' up.

440
00:32:29.748 --> 00:32:30.840
Mm.

441
00:32:31.717 --> 00:32:34.481
I'm workin' on the perfect sauce.

442
00:32:35.387 --> 00:32:36.547
Yeah.

443
00:32:37.456 --> 00:32:39.287
That'll put me on the Food Channel.

444
00:32:40.859 --> 00:32:43.350
Put this pplace back on the mapp
where it belongs.

445
00:32:43.428 --> 00:32:44.725
I'll talk to you later.

446
00:32:56.408 --> 00:32:59.673
Can I interest y'all in a plate of
soon-to-be-award-winnin' barbecue?

447
00:33:06.785 --> 00:33:08.582
You're from Dinky's. ain't ya?

448
00:33:09.588 --> 00:33:10.850
Well. you tell that sumbitch.

449
00:33:10.922 --> 00:33:13.516
he thinks he's gonna come over here
and get my recippes...

450
00:33:14.526 --> 00:33:17.825
well. I got a double-barreled answer
to his query right inside.

451
00:33:21.133 --> 00:33:22.964
God damn. that's good.

452
00:33:28.340 --> 00:33:29.830
Doctor Block!

453
00:33:29.908 --> 00:33:32.741
Three fresh ones rollin' in!

454
00:33:32.811 --> 00:33:33.937
Christ. you're kidding.

455
00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:36.242
Automobile accident
off of Highway 18.

456
00:33:36.315 --> 00:33:37.714
DOAs?

457
00:33:37.783 --> 00:33:39.182
Have Andy pick 'em up.

458
00:33:39.251 --> 00:33:41.947
He's already on 620
picking up another two.

459
00:33:42.921 --> 00:33:44.616
Fucking Wednesday nights.

460
00:33:46.358 --> 00:33:48.292
That's unsanitary. Doc.

461
00:33:48.360 --> 00:33:50.294
Not if I'm the only one using it.

462
00:33:50.362 --> 00:33:52.660
Helps me monitor
my state of calmness.

463
00:33:52.731 --> 00:33:55.199
Yeah. don't get all worked up
enough to crack it.

464
00:33:55.267 --> 00:33:56.256
Fuck.

465
00:33:56.335 --> 00:33:58.394
You might cut yourself pretty good.

466
00:33:58.470 --> 00:34:00.563
Then I'd know I was not calm.

467
00:34:07.112 --> 00:34:09.444
Yeah. what do you say now. Doc?

468
00:34:10.916 --> 00:34:12.907
Somebody call my wife.

469
00:34:31.803 --> 00:34:33.100
DC-2?

470
00:34:34.306 --> 00:34:35.432
Mm.

471
00:34:37.109 --> 00:34:38.133
Yeah.

472
00:34:40.145 --> 00:34:42.545
Well. what about
countering with atroppine?

473
00:34:45.517 --> 00:34:46.609
Yeah.

474
00:34:49.688 --> 00:34:51.588
Okay. Gotcha. gotcha.

475
00:34:53.558 --> 00:34:56.083
Well. boys. I'm beat.

476
00:34:56.161 --> 00:34:58.925
I gotta get home.
I'll see y'all tomorrow.

477
00:34:58.997 --> 00:35:01.329
All right. then.
Thanks for the extra help. Earl.

478
00:35:01.400 --> 00:35:03.061
Hey. Wray.

479
00:35:03.135 --> 00:35:04.762
You in trouble again?

480
00:35:04.836 --> 00:35:06.929
Just passin' through. I hope.

481
00:35:07.005 --> 00:35:08.131
Well. me. too.

482
00:35:08.206 --> 00:35:09.366
How's the wife. Earl?

483
00:35:12.010 --> 00:35:13.841
Well. she's not too good.

484
00:35:13.912 --> 00:35:15.004
Thanks for askin'.

485
00:35:16.548 --> 00:35:18.641
Most of it's her own doin'. you know.

486
00:35:18.717 --> 00:35:20.810
Smokin' them goddamn cigarettes.

487
00:35:20.886 --> 00:35:22.513
Pack a day for 40 years.

488
00:35:23.655 --> 00:35:27.022
Yeah. she doesn't want anything
to do with. uh...chemo.

489
00:35:27.092 --> 00:35:31.051
So...it does take its toll.

490
00:35:31.129 --> 00:35:33.222
You don't smoke. do you. Wray?

491
00:35:34.166 --> 00:35:35.224
No.

492
00:35:36.101 --> 00:35:38.831
That's probably good.

493
00:35:40.939 --> 00:35:42.270
See y'all.

494
00:35:45.010 --> 00:35:46.443
You're gonna start by telling me

495
00:35:46.511 --> 00:35:48.206
when you first started
carrying this gun.

496
00:35:49.815 --> 00:35:51.544
And then we'll move up

497
00:35:51.616 --> 00:35:54.050
to when you first set eyes
on this gal Cherry.

498
00:36:38.864 --> 00:36:40.195
Okay.

499
00:36:40.966 --> 00:36:42.194
Okay.

500
00:36:52.410 --> 00:36:53.604
Sheriff Hague.

501
00:36:53.678 --> 00:36:55.475
It's J.t. Sheriff.

502
00:36:55.547 --> 00:36:57.606
J.T.. how's the barbecue business?

503
00:36:59.084 --> 00:37:02.110
Ever since that bastard landlord
raised the rent. it's gone to shit.

504
00:37:02.187 --> 00:37:04.246
Well. I'm real sorry
to hear about that.

505
00:37:04.322 --> 00:37:05.721
I wish there was something
I could do.

506
00:37:06.825 --> 00:37:09.157
Right now I ain't callin' my brother.
I'm callin' the sheriff.

507
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:11.593
I'm listening. What's the trouble?

508
00:37:11.663 --> 00:37:13.961
Well. there ain't no trouble.
Not yet. anyway.

509
00:37:14.032 --> 00:37:16.694
I got two delinquents been hangin'
around here for over an hour.

510
00:37:16.768 --> 00:37:18.895
They won't purchase
and they won't leave.

511
00:37:20.605 --> 00:37:22.334
Oh. never mind. Here they come.

512
00:37:22.407 --> 00:37:25.843
You cook that meat
at 250 degrees. don't you?

513
00:37:25.911 --> 00:37:28.607
I don't remember.
I set the heat with my hand.

514
00:37:28.680 --> 00:37:31.513
You give me that recipe. or I'll raise
your rent higher than a Georgia pine.

515
00:37:31.583 --> 00:37:34.051
Brother. ain't no Texan's ever gonna
give you his barbecue recipe.

516
00:37:34.119 --> 00:37:36.280
That's a fact.
He'll take it to his grave.

517
00:37:36.354 --> 00:37:38.788
I could be bleedin' like a stuck pig.
I ain't gonna tell you.

518
00:37:38.857 --> 00:37:41.485
I could be dyin' in your arms.
I ain't gonna tell you!

519
00:37:41.560 --> 00:37:43.289
- Heh heh heh.
- We'll see about that.

520
00:37:47.465 --> 00:37:48.523
You gonna look.

521
00:37:50.168 --> 00:37:51.635
or you gonna eat?

522
00:38:00.278 --> 00:38:01.609
You called for me?

523
00:38:01.680 --> 00:38:03.511
I need for you to see this.

524
00:38:05.884 --> 00:38:07.408
Looks like a no-brainer.

525
00:38:07.485 --> 00:38:08.884
What does that mean?

526
00:38:08.954 --> 00:38:10.546
No brain.

527
00:38:10.622 --> 00:38:13.318
Scoopped clean out of her skull.

528
00:38:13.391 --> 00:38:15.120
Oh. oh. oh!
I know what this is.

529
00:38:15.193 --> 00:38:17.718
Don't tell me.
Uh... Iiquefactive necrosis.

530
00:38:18.930 --> 00:38:20.124
You think?

531
00:38:20.198 --> 00:38:21.358
Oh. sure. yeah.

532
00:38:21.433 --> 00:38:23.025
Thank you. That'll be all.

533
00:38:31.543 --> 00:38:32.874
Oh...

534
00:38:37.015 --> 00:38:39.176
Did you know she was back in town?

535
00:38:41.119 --> 00:38:42.279
No.

